Package: ncfigR
Title: NC-Style Bioinformatics Figure Toolkit
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Jiang", family = "Congxin", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "jcx981212@163.com")
Author: Jiang Congxin
Maintainer: Jiang Congxin <jcx981212@163.com>
Description: Provides lightweight ggplot2 and patchwork helpers for building
    Nature Communications-inspired bioinformatics figure panels from traceable
    source-data tables, including embedding, composition, marker heatmap,
    ligand-receptor, trajectory, and benchmark panels.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/jiangcongxin/ncfigR
BugReports: https://github.com/jiangcongxin/ncfigR/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: ggplot2, patchwork, dplyr, tidyr, readr, scales, ggrepel,
        igraph, ggraph, rlang, grDevices, svglite
Suggests: ComplexHeatmap, circlize, Seurat, SeuratObject, cowplot,
        testthat (>= 3.0.0), knitr, rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
NeedsCompilation: no
